Package opennlp.ccg.synsem

Interface Summary
Arg An interface for objects that can be arguments in a category.
Category A CCG category.
CategoryFcn A set of functions that can be applied to Categories.
LexSemOrigin An interface for items which introduce lexical semantics, covering (lexical) signs and unary type changing rules.
LF An interface for objects which represent Logical Forms.
Modality A modality that can decorate a categorial slash.
ReRankingScorer Interface for signs scorers with both a base model and a full (reranking) model.
SignScorer Interface for sign scoring models.
TargetCat A category that can be a target of a curried cat.
 

Class Summary
AbstractCat Abstract category adapter for CCG categories.
ArgStack A stack of arguments with their associated slashes.
AtomCat The most basic CG category.
BasicArg A basic argument that contains a slash and a category.
CategoryFcnAdapter An adapter for Category Functions so that you only have to implement the methods you want.
CatReader Utility class to build categories.
ComplexCat A non-recursive representation of complex categories.
DerivationHandler<T> A class to simplify implementing a recursive procedure on a derivation.
Dollar A variable representing a stack of arguments
GenerativeSyntacticModel A class implementing a variant of Hockenmaier's HWDep generative syntactic model, with additional postag variables.
GenerativeSyntacticModel.FactorsGetter Derivation handler for getting the factors for each derivation step as a list of words.
GenerativeSyntacticModel.GenLogProb Class for caching the model's log prob in a sign.
LexLogProbFeatureExtractor A class for extracting total lexical log probabilities from a supertagger as a feature.
SetArg A category which contains an unordered set of categories.
Sign A CCG sign, consisting of a list of words paired with a category.
Sign.FilledDeps Filled dependencies wrapper, for unique retrieval from data objects.
Sign.UnfilledDeps Unfilled dependencies wrapper, for unique retrieval from data objects.
SignHash A set of signs, unique up to surface words.
Slash A categorial slash which has an optional mode associated with it.
SlashMode A mode that can decorate a categorial slash.
SyntacticFeatureExtractor A class for extracting generic features from derivations, inspired by those in the C&C-07 normal form model.
SyntacticFeatureExtractor.FeatureMapWrapper Feature map wrapper, for unique retrieval from a sign's data objects.
VarModality A class for variables which can stand for slash modalities.
